# 3. ブライダルフェスタへようこそ！

Honami: (It's almost time for the others to arrive.)
Honami: (I didn't want to be late, and ended up coming a little too early...)
Honami: (Anyway, Ms. Yoisaki and her friend should be...)
Kanade: Oh, there she is. Thank you for waiting, Ms. Mochizuki.
Honami: Ms. Yoisaki!
Honami: It's okay. I just arrived not long ago.
Honami: Also, is the person you invited already here...?
Kanade: I'm not sure. I received a message saying that they're almost here...
???: Oh, there they are! Over here!
Mizuki: Hey, Kanade! And this is...
Honami: Oh, I'm...
Mizuki: Honami Mochizuki, right?!
Honami: Huh?
Kanade: Oh, I'm sorry. I've mentioned you in conversation to everyone a few times already.
Mizuki: Ena has too! I've heard all about how nice a person you are!
Honami: Oh, really...? I feel a little embarrassed now...
Mizuki: Haha! But it's really nice to finally meet you after hearing everyone's stories!
Mizuki: Oh, I still haven't introduced myself. I'm Mizuki Akiyama. I'm in the same music group as Kanade and mainly work as the video editor.
Honami: Yes, I've also heard your name in passing. It's nice to meet you, and I hope we have fun today.
Mizuki: Yeah, same!
Mizuki: Oh, also... Thanks for letting me tag along today! I've actually had my eye on this fair for a while now.
Honami: No, a friend gave me this ticket... Also, I'm glad that you decided to join us since it's always fun to go to these things as a group.
Honami: Akiyama...? Is something wrong...?
Mizuki: Nothing's wrong! I was just thinking that you really are a super nice person, Honami.
Honami: Huh...? R-Really...?
Mizuki: Yes, really!
Mizuki: Kanade, I hope you know how lucky you are to be in the care of such a nice girl.
Kanade: Huh...? I, um... I'm sorry. I do appreciate everything you do, but that might not have come across properly...
Honami: No, don't say that! I know that you do...!
Kanade: You do? Then, I'm glad...
Mizuki: Oh, looks like the bus is here. Let's hop on!
Honami: Okay. This fair's going to be so much fun.
Mizuki: Yeah, it is!
Mizuki: Whoa...! So this is a bridal fair!
Kanade: Wow, there's so many people...
Honami: And it's not just couples here. I'm also seeing a lot of families and groups of friends.
Mizuki: Yeah! It looks like a fun event for all ages.
Honami: Hehe. It certainly does. Now, where should we begin?
Mizuki: Based on this map, the dress exhibit is straight ahead... To the left is all the accessory shops...
Mizuki: Oh, hey! They even have a wedding hall that you can check out! I'd love to see that!
Kanade: There's so much to do...
Honami: Yes, and every booth also seems to have quite a lot to offer. It may be difficult to see everything in one day...
Mizuki: Yeah. You two have until this evening, right?
Honami: Yes, since I'm also scheduled to work today. I plan to head over to Ms. Yoisaki's house this evening after spending the day here.
Mizuki: Then, instead of trying to see everything in the time we have, we should probably prioritize the things we really wanna check out.
Mizuki: So, where do you two wanna go?
Kanade: I'll leave this up to you two since I haven't really read up on this fair.
Honami: There are a couple places I'd like to go, but the map says they're pretty far from here... So, Akiyama, why don't we start with what you'd like to see?
Mizuki: Really?! Thanks! Then, mind if we check out the dress exhibit first?
Mizuki: On top of the dresses made by famous designers, they have some that were made by amateurs who did well in their contest. I really wanna see those!
Kanade: Yes, wedding dresses... I've never seen one up close before, so that could be fun.
Honami: Hehe. Then, shall we?
Mizuki: Whoa...!
Mizuki: I don't believe it! This is so awesome! Look at all these dresses on display...! And they're all absolutely gorgeous!
Honami: Yes, they are...
Honami: It's hard not to be overwhelmed by how glamorous they are when you're this close.
Mizuki: Haha. I get what you mean! I mean, check out the skirt on this one!
Kanade: The skirt?
Mizuki: It's called a princess cut. These are the kinds of dresses with super fluffy skirts that you see a lot in fairy tales! And the bow on the back of this one is so cute!
Kanade: Yes, it's so big.
Mizuki: I know, right?! Oh, this one's a pantsuit dress! Talk about trendy! And the lace on the back's so detailed!
Mizuki: Oh, it even has slits! I really like that. It gives it more of a mature feel.
Honami: Akiyama seems to be enjoying this very much.
Kanade: Mizuki likes cute clothing a lot. Just looking at that excitement makes me glad I was able to invite an extra friend.
Mizuki: Haha. Sorry, you two...! I sort of don't know what to do with myself...
Honami: No, I understand how you feel since I also occasionally make my own clothes.
Mizuki: You do?! So do I! We could totally be sewing buddies!
Kanade: Yes, I have a feeling that you two would get along really well. On the other hand, I don't really understand the appeal of dresses...
Mizuki: No, Kanade, don't say that! I really want you to see how amazing these wedding dresses are too!
Mizuki: Oh, I know! It'd involve me talking a lot, but what if I commentate as we walk around? That might make things more fun!
Kanade: Oh, sure... That might really help.
Mizuki: Awesome! Then, let's start with the skirt on this mermaid dress! It's called that because...
Honami: *Sigh* They had so many dresses just in that one exhibit.
Kanade: Yes, and I learned so much. It was fun having you explain each one, Mizuki.
Mizuki: Really? That's great to hear! Well, there's a bunch of other stuff left to check out, so wanna head over to our next stop?!
Honami: Yes, let's!
Honami: These must be the accessory shops... They have tiaras, bracelets, necklaces... And they're all so beautiful...
Mizuki: Oh, you can even try them on. Kanade, let's see how this tiara looks on you!
Kanade: Wait, me...? Sure, but...
Honami: Oh wow...! It looks so pretty on you, Ms. Yoisaki.
Mizuki: She's right! You don't dress up enough, Kanade! So, since we're here, try on this necklace! And this bracelet!
Kanade: Okay, but... Oh, they're so heavy...
Mizuki: Haha! Don't worry! They look amazing on you!
Honami: Hehe. You'd probably look like a real princess if you were to put one of those dresses on.
Kanade: Y-You think so...?
Mizuki: That workshop was so much fun! And we got to make these matching bracelets!
Kanade: Thank you both for helping me with the tricky parts. Mine wouldn't have turned out this well if you hadn't.
Mizuki: Honami deserves most of the credit. I saw you had nimble fingers, but you also did a really great job of explaining what to do. You were like everyone's favorite kindergarten teacher.
Honami: R-Really...? That might be because I actually taught kindergarten for a day. Anyway, I'm glad I could help.
Kanade: Hm? What's going on over there? A lot of people seem to be gathering...
Honami: Let's see... That seems to be the fashion show for wedding dresses and tuxedos. How about we go take a quick look since we're here?
Mizuki: Okay!
Mizuki: This is way too much fun! And we haven't even covered half of it! Talk about an amazing fair!
Honami: Yes, every booth had such interesting things to see. Where should we go ne—
Honami: Oh...
Honami: (Is she starting to get tired...? We have been walking nonstop since this morning. Also, Ms. Yoisaki isn't particularly fond of crowds...)
Honami: Oh, that reminds me. The corner for the bouquet exhibit's supposed to be around here somewhere. I was hoping to take a look at it, so would it be okay if we went there next?
Mizuki: Ooh, I wanna check it out too! How about you, Kanade?
Kanade: Oh, um... Sure...
Mizuki: Wow, these are so pretty...! They've got so many different types too. Round, oval and even wreaths!
Kanade: Yes, not only that... It smells very nice here somehow...
Honami: It must be all the fresh-cut flowers. The roses, the lilies of the valley... So many gentle fragrances all mixing together. It's very soothing.
Mizuki: Yeah, definitely! And there aren't that many people here, probably since this exhibit's way in the back. We can relax here for a bit.
Kanade: Yes, that sounds nice...
Kanade: Oh...
Kanade: Thank you, Ms. Mochizuki...
Mizuki: *Sigh* We saw so much. It's almost noon, so let's find a place where we can sit and have lunch.
Mizuki: Do you know if there's anywhere good around here?
Honami: Oh, there's a nice-looking cafe right by this event center. Rumor has it that the food's very good.
Mizuki: Nice! Honami with the good intel! Alright, let's go check it out!
Kanade: Okay.
Mizuki: And after we've had a filling lunch, let's get right back to it and make the most of our afternoon!
Honami: Yes, let's!
